<number box="[912,970,1786,1811]" pageId="4" pageNumber="90" value="1966.0">1966</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
based his redescription of 
<taxonomicName authority="Seguy" authorityName="Seguy" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Chirosiomima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="90" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gestroi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="90">Chirosiomima gestroi</emphasis>
(Séguy)
</taxonomicName>
, with illustrations of the male and female genitalia, on specimens in the Stuttgart Museum collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[183,228,1859,1882]" name="Iran" pageId="4" pageNumber="90">Iran</collectingCountry>
in 
<number box="[271,327,1858,1883]" pageId="4" pageNumber="90" value="1954.0">1954</number>
by W. Richter &amp; F. Schäuffele. This was unfortunate, as the present study revealed significant differences in the male and female terminalia between specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[960,1043,1894,1919]" name="Tunisia" pageId="4" pageNumber="90">Tunisia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1100,1148,1895,1918]" name="Iran" pageId="4" pageNumber="90">Iran</collectingCountry>
, respectively. As detailed below, Hennig’s redescription of “ 
<taxonomicName authority="Seguy" authorityName="Seguy" box="[558,776,1931,1955]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Chirosiomima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="90" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gestroi">
<emphasis box="[558,673,1931,1954]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="90">C. gestroi</emphasis>
(Séguy)
</taxonomicName>
” refers actually to a different species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Emden, 1941" authorityName="Emden" authorityYear="1941" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Pegomyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="90" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscurinervis">
<emphasis box="[1245,1436,1930,1954]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="90">C. obscurinervis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Emden" box="[158,313,1966,1991]" pageId="4" pageNumber="90" refString="Emden, F. I. van (1941) Keys to the Muscidae of the Ethiopian Region: Scatophaginae, Anthomyiinae, Lispinae, Fanniinae. Bulletin of Entomological Research, 32, 251 - 275. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1017 / s 0007485300017193" type="journal article" year="1941">
Emden, 
<number box="[253,313,1967,1991]" pageId="4" pageNumber="90" value="1941.0">1941</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
